The 1.8% decline in June in the catering sector only worsened in July.
Pubs and bars where alcoholic beverages are served are by far the most popular, with more points of resemblance than restaurants that fall.
Food pubs also suffered from the effects of the sun, but not as much as restaurateurs.
It seems like people just want to go out for a drink.
In pubs and bars, beverage sales increased by 6.6% over the month and food declined by 3%.”
Paul Newman, RSM Leisure and Hospitality Analyst, said: “These results follow the trend observed since late April.
The weather and the impact of major social or sporting events remain the most important factors when it comes to sales in the off-home market.
