A tsunami also struck west of Donggala in 1996, killing nine people.
Indonesia is located on the Pacific Seismic Fire Circle and is regularly shaken by earthquakes.
Here are some of the major earthquakes and tsunamis of recent years:
2004: A major earthquake, which occurred on December 26 on the west coast of the Indonesian province of Aceh, triggered a tsunami that swept across 14 countries, killing 226,000 people along the Indian Ocean coastline, more than half of whom were in Aceh.
2005: Several violent earthquakes shook the west coast of Sumatra from late March to early April.
