2006: An earthquake with a magnitude of 6.8 hit southern Java, Indonesia's most populated island, triggering a tsunami that hit the southern coast and claimed nearly 700 lives.
2009: An earthquake with a magnitude of 7.6 rocked the city of Padang, capital of West Sumatra province.
